   The Debate

Back to square one? Trump-Kim summit ends with no agreement

   Issued on: 28/02/2019 - 20:02
   (BUTTON)
   By: Tom Burges WATSON Follow

   The Hanoi summit between US President Donald Trump and North Korea's
   Kim Jong-un had started amidst great optimism. But it came to an abrupt
   end on Thursday morning. So what went wrong? Does this mean we're now
   back to square one? Was Trump right to walk away? And should the US
   president really be travelling 13,000 kilometres - in each direction -
   without all the necessary groundwork being laid beforehand?
   Advertising

   Produced by Alessandro XENOS, Selina SYKES and Ingri BERGO.
     * North Korea
     * Donald Trump
     * Kim Jong-un

   Our guests
     * Annick CIZEL, Senior Lecturer, Paris Sorbonne Nouvelle University

